Theoverall current account surplus in Asia's 11 largest economiesdropped from 6.3 percent of aggregate GDP in 2007 to 1.6 percentlast year, according to Nomura's calculations. Japan's onceformidable surplus has dropped almost to zero and India,Indonesia and Hong Kong have all slipped into deficit.
